Installing Flexlay 
==================

Requirements:
=============

To compile Flexlay you need:

Build Tools:
  * GCC/G++ or Clang C++ compiler
  * SCons (build system)
  * SWIG (for Ruby bindings)
  * pkg-config

Libraries:
  * Ruby development headers (ruby-dev)
  * Boost development headers (libboost-dev)
  * OpenGL/Mesa development headers
  * X11 development headers (includes libx11, libxmu, libxi, libxxf86vm, libxrandr)
  * PNG and JPEG libraries

On Ubuntu/Debian, install dependencies with:

  $ sudo apt install build-essential libboost-dev ruby-dev scons swig \
      libx11-dev libxmu-dev libxi-dev libxxf86vm-dev libxrandr-dev \
      libgl1-mesa-dev libglu1-mesa-dev libpng-dev libjpeg-dev


Compilation:
============

The project uses a bundled copy of ClanLib (included in external/clanlib/).
To build:

  $ scons

This will automatically:
  1. Build the bundled ClanLib libraries with position-independent code
  2. Compile the Flexlay library and tools
  3. Generate Ruby bindings for game editors


Building ClanLib Separately (optional):
========================================

If you need to rebuild ClanLib independently:

  $ cd external/clanlib
  $ scons
  $ cd ../..


Running:
========

The directories supertux/, netpanzer/, paint/ contain the editors for 
the games. Run the executable scripts in those directories. You may need 
to adjust the path to the game data, which is currently hardcoded in 
the scripts.


Installation:
==============

Currently not supported. Run directly from the source directory.


Notes:
======

Flexlay is still a moving target, so most often you are better off
using the latest development version instead of a tarball release.

The bundled ClanLib version has been patched for modern C++ and is 
included in external/clanlib/. Building with system ClanLib is not 
recommended.

